  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed combinations. All thirteen credibility factors are addressed; seven factors were formally assessed and six were scoped out as outside the current validation boundary. Decision: Accepted with documented residual uncertainty.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-absolute-prediction",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-measurements",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/hemolysis-index-experimental-series"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "type": "ContextOfUse",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment. The pump is operated at blood temperatures between 36 °C and 38 °C, inlet static pressures ranging from 5 mmHg to 20 mmHg, and volumetric flow rates spanning 3 L/min to 7 L/min at rotational speeds of 2400 RPM to 3200 RPM. Blood viscosity is treated as a Newtonian fluid with dynamic viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s. Flow regime is laminar-to-transitional (Re 200–1800 at the impeller tip). These ranges are enumerated in the description to characterise the simulation domain; the model has been exercised within these bands during internal sensitivity studies.",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "decisionConsequence": "High"
  },
